<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="68" type="distribution in canada and alaska">
<paragraph pageId="37" pageNumber="68">Distribution in Canada and Alaska.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="37" pageNumber="68">
ON, QC, NB (
<bibRefCitation author="Bousquet, Y" journalOrPublisher="Sofia-Moscow" pageId="39" pageNumber="70" title="Checklist of beetles (Coleoptera) of Canada and Alaska" year="2013">Bousquet et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Rugilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Rugilus ceylanensis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ceylanensis">Rugilus ceylanensis</taxonomicName>
occurs in the southern and eastern Palaearctic and Oriental regions, New Guinea, and Hawaii where it is adventive (
<bibRefCitation author="Hoebeke, ER" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington" pageId="41" pageNumber="72" pagination="508 - 516" title="Rugilusceylanensis (Kraatz) (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae): a south Asian rove beetle new to North America." url="10.4289/0013-8797.112.4.508" volume="112" year="2010">Hoebeke 2010</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Assing, V" journalOrPublisher="Stuttgarter Beitraege zur Naturkunde A (Neue Serie)" pageId="39" pageNumber="70" pagination="115 - 190" title="The Rugilus species of the Palaearctic and Oriental regions (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae)." volume="5" year="2012">Assing 2012</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Hoebeke, ER" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington" pageId="41" pageNumber="72" pagination="508 - 516" title="Rugilusceylanensis (Kraatz) (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae): a south Asian rove beetle new to North America." url="10.4289/0013-8797.112.4.508" volume="112" year="2010">Hoebeke (2010)</bibRefCitation>
reported this adventive species for the first time for North America from several states in the USA, and ON and QC in Canada.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="68" type="natural history">
<paragraph pageId="37" pageNumber="68">Natural history.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="37" pageNumber="68">
All specimens of 
<taxonomicName genus="Rugilis" lsidName="Rugilis ceylanensis" pageId="37" pageNumber="68" rank="species" species="ceylanensis">Rugilis ceylanensis</taxonomicName>
from NB were collected from a pile of decaying moldy corncobs and cornhusks. Elsewhere in the USA and Canada, this species was found in leaf piles, rotten leaves and logs, detritus, horse dung, and carrion (
<bibRefCitation author="Hoebeke, ER" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington" pageId="41" pageNumber="72" pagination="508 - 516" title="Rugilusceylanensis (Kraatz) (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae): a south Asian rove beetle new to North America." url="10.4289/0013-8797.112.4.508" volume="112" year="2010">Hoebeke 2010</bibRefCitation>
), and at the edge of an orchard growing apples, pears, and plums (coll. C. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lévesque">Levesque</normalizedToken>
). In Europe, adults were found in compost heaps, mammal dung, carrion, and along lakeshores and riverbanks (
<bibRefCitation author="Assing, V" journalOrPublisher="Stuttgarter Beitraege zur Naturkunde A (Neue Serie)" pageId="39" pageNumber="70" pagination="115 - 190" title="The Rugilus species of the Palaearctic and Oriental regions (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae)." volume="5" year="2012">Assing 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
